   {:e #blake3 "215c22c1b3ee27f5ce214c41246c73a445c47a89cabfc04273e075444bc42a20" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Comprehensive test suite for the entire C9 second-order epistemic closure pipeline. Every component gets unit tests, the full pipeline gets integration tests, and the E2E script validates the complete user experience. STRUCTURE — 4 TEST LAYERS: LAYER 1: UNIT TESTS FOR C9-P1 (agent provenance, in concept.rs test section). 6 tests: (A) test_agent_groups_single_agent — 5 observations from one agent, one group with 5 members. (B) test_agent_groups_multi_agent — 8 observations from 3 agents, 3 groups with correct member counts. (C) test_agreement_cluster_formation — 3 agents each observe 'F(S) monotonicity is false' with different wording, similarity > 0.4, one cluster forms with agreement=3/3. Log: all pairwise similarities, cluster formation steps, final cluster membership. (D) test_agreement_no_false_positive — 3 agents observe completely unrelated topics, no cluster exceeds agreement=1/3. Log: all pairwise similarities (should all be < threshold). (E) test_agreement_score_monotonic — proptest: for any set of observations, adding a corroborating observation never decreases agreement_score. (F) test_agreement_idempotent — running find_agreement_clusters twice produces identical results. LAYER 2: UNIT TESTS FOR C9-P2 (link extraction, in concept.rs test section). 6 tests: (A) test_extract_task_link — body with 't-abcd1234 depends on t-efgh5678' produces DependsOn link. (B) test_extract_spec_link — body with 'see INV-STORE-001' produces RelatesTo link to spec entity. (C) test_extract_no_refs — body without references returns empty vec. (D) test_extract_dedup — same ref mentioned 3 times produces 1 link. (E) test_extract_relationship_keywords — 'requires INV-X' -> DependsOn, 'blocks t-Y' -> Blocks, 'see also t-Z' -> RelatesTo. (F) test_extract_idempotent — running twice produces identical links. LAYER 3: UNIT TESTS FOR C9-P3 (seed integration, in seed.rs test section). 5 tests: (A) test_seed_backward_compat — single-agent store produces IDENTICAL seed output before and after C9 changes. This is the MOST CRITICAL test. Capture seed output from current code, commit as golden file, verify new code matches exactly with empty corroboration map. (B) test_seed_corroboration_boost — entity in 3-agent agreement cluster ranks higher than equally-relevant entity with no corroboration. Log: both entities full score breakdown (relevance, significance, recency, corroboration). (C) test_seed_convergent_section — with agreement data, Orientation section contains 'Convergent findings' subsection. (D) test_seed_budget_preserves_convergent — under tight budget (200 tokens), convergent findings survive when State entries are dropped. Log: token counts per section before and after compression. (E) test_seed_empty_corroboration_fallback — proptest: for any store, score_entity with empty corroboration map == current formula within f64::EPSILON. LAYER 4: UNIT TESTS FOR C9-5 (stagnation, already exists as t-1a20a2e9 dependency). Verify: 4 tests as specified in C9-5 task description. INTEGRATION TEST (new file tests/c9_second_order.rs): Full pipeline test. Steps: (1) Create Store::genesis(). (2) Create 3 AgentIds: agent_a = AgentId::from_name('audit-agent-1'), agent_b, agent_c. (3) Each agent transacts 2 observations about the same topic ('F(S) stagnation') with slightly different wording. (4) Agent_a also transacts 1 unique observation about an unrelated topic. (5) Run agent_observation_groups(store) — verify 3 groups. (6) Run find_agreement_clusters(store, 0.4) — verify 1 cluster with 3 agents for the shared topic, 0 clusters for the unique observation. (7) Run extract_observation_links(store) — verify any cross-references in observation bodies produce links. (8) Build seed via assemble_seed with corroboration data — verify Convergent findings section exists, shared topic ranks above unique observation. (9) Run detect_stagnation with flat trajectory — verify StagnationSignal emitted. DIAGNOSTIC LOGGING: Every test function logs to stderr with structured format: [C9-TEST] test_name: step_description | key=value. Example: [C9-TEST] agreement_cluster_formation: pairwise_similarity | obs_a=0x1234 obs_b=0x5678 similarity=0.72. Example: [C9-TEST] seed_corroboration_boost: score_breakdown | entity=0x1234 relevance=0.6 significance=0.3 recency=0.8 corroboration=0.9 total=0.58. On failure: dump full store state (datom count, entity list, observation bodies) to help diagnose root cause. E2E SCRIPT (scripts/e2e_c9_second_order.sh): (1) braid init in temp directory. (2) braid observe 'F(S) has been stagnant at 0.62' --agent audit-1 -c 0.9. (3) braid observe 'Fitness score stuck at 0.62 for 13 sessions' --agent audit-2 -c 0.85. (4) braid observe 'F(S) not moving, verification sprint needed' --agent audit-3 -c 0.9. (5) braid observe 'Unrelated finding about C8 violation' --agent audit-1 -c 0.8. (6) braid status -q | grep 'agents' (should show corroboration data). (7) braid seed --task 'synthesize findings' (should surface F(S) stagnation as convergent). (8) Assert exit codes, grep for expected output patterns. (9) Log all outputs with timestamps for debugging. ACCEPTANCE: (A) All 23+ unit tests pass. (B) Integration test passes. (C) E2E script exits 0 with all assertions. (D) Zero regressions in existing 2043 tests. (E) cargo clippy clean. DEPENDS-ON: C9-P1 (t-7f200105), C9-P2 (t-fa7eb30a), C9-P3 (t-5dcc97ae), C9-5 (t-1a20a2e9). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/tests/c9_second_order.rs, scripts/e2e_c9_second_order.sh, plus inline tests in concept.rs, seed.rs, methodology.rs. EFFORT: 5h." :op :assert}
